WWE Clash at the Castle is live from Glasgow, Scotland.

![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d56e145f80b7500016ba502/36fe8d53-8780-4459-802d-e96902e3cabd/20240615_111825.jpg?format=original)

*   ## **_WWE CHAMPIONSHIP I QUIT MATCH: CODY RHODES(c) DEF. AJ STYLES_**
    

Cody and AJ kick the match off by brawling to the backstage area to the international announcers area.

![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d56e145f80b7500016ba502/60d0e818-8e76-4643-b164-6995dd6880df/20240615_112238.jpg?format=original)

They’re back in the Arena when AJ Styles hits a brainbuster on Cody onto the announce table.

Camera cuts to AJ Styles arguing with Cody Rhodes and when it cuts back to Cody... HES BUSTED OPEN BAD!!!!!!!!

MASSIVE \*F\*\*K YOU AJ\* CHANTS!!

![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d56e145f80b7500016ba502/3d055c03-c68a-4479-9d3d-f95f89511356/received_439503288945770.jpeg?format=original)

AJ Styles brings out handcuffs which gets a **Kinky Bastard** chant and he beats on Cody with a Kendo stick. Cody's mom distracts AJ long enough for Cody to get his self back together.

![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d56e145f80b7500016ba502/2debc769-bdb1-49b9-82d0-39b5830e2dcf/20240615_113759.jpg?format=original)

AJ is busted open. Cody handcuffs AJ to the ropes. Beats him with a chair and threatened to hit him with steel steps.

AJ QUITS.

CODY HITS HIM ANYWAY.

![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d56e145f80b7500016ba502/178d068c-da4a-43c6-af8f-3bc98f02c8e2/20240615_114717.jpg?format=original)

Cody is attacked by the Bloodline until Randy Orton and Kevin Owens come out to even the odds.

* * *

![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d56e145f80b7500016ba502/297ca7e6-4159-41af-96bf-1454994f3138/20240615_120116.jpg?format=original)

*   ## **_WWE WOMENS TAG TEAM CHAMPIONSHIP: ALBA FYRE AND ISLA DAWN DEF. JADE CARGILL AND BIANCA BELAIR(c) vs SHAYNA BASZLER AND ZOEY STARKS_**
    

Pretty fun match that really fell apart in the final minutes.

![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d56e145f80b7500016ba502/424b496c-5853-43a1-9836-112df6e2ae15/20240615_121148.jpg?format=original)

* * *

![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d56e145f80b7500016ba502/b80c8390-0d7e-4f69-be91-6f61baac585e/20240615_122941.jpg?format=original)

*   ## **_WWE INTERCONTINENTAL CHAMPIONSHIP: SAMI ZAYN(c) DEF. CHAD GABLE_**
    

Excellent wrestling match sprinkled with all the drama of one of WWE's best ongoing stories.

At one point Chad Gable is berating Maxxine for not whacking Sami with the IC Belt off a distraction.

Otis will not allow this and gets in Gable's face. Later, Gable gets thrown into Maxxine's bad ankle. Otis has had enough of Maxxine getting hurt. He takes her and leaves. This distraction allows Sami to hit Gable with the Helluva Kick to win.

![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d56e145f80b7500016ba502/ad55af16-78b6-43e7-bd29-48b96650d975/Screenshot_20240615_124135.jpg?format=original)

* * *

![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d56e145f80b7500016ba502/7812dbbb-9047-4fac-a83f-15ee783998cc/20240615_131516.jpg?format=original)

*   ## **_WWE WOMEN'S CHAMPIONSHIP: BAYLEY(c) DEF. PIPER NIVEN_**
    

Great showing for both Bayley and Piper Niven tonight. Chelsea gets ejected early on allowing this to be a straight up back and forth match for the most part.

![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d56e145f80b7500016ba502/285195d4-6d40-4d69-b7b9-7a7e1d219960/20240615_131202.jpg?format=original)

Chelsea does make her way back out under a mask to distract the ref and cost Bayley a pinfall. But it wasn’t enough to help Piper win

Bayley ends the match with an uncharacteristic Crucifix Bomb.

* * *

![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d56e145f80b7500016ba502/8f665818-305a-4f3c-9ccd-f571c40e6b52/20240615_133400.jpg?format=original)

*   ## **_WWE WORLD HEAVYWEIGHT CHAMPIONSHIP: DAMIEN PRIEST(c) vs DREW MCINTYRE_**
    

Priest and McIntyre are having an excellent big man match. Even considering Priest mightve legitimately hurt himself on a botched dove early on.

At one point, the ref goes out and a ref comes in… But it’s CM Punk.

Punk kicks McIntyre in the balls and costs him the World Championship